docs.abstract: Hacker working under pseudonym Guccifer 2.0 makes public set of internal Democratic Party documents that contain personal contact information of almost 200 lawmakers; hacker is believed to have ties to Russian intelligence services and appears eager to taunt Democrats, indicating more leaks will be made available in future.

docs.abstract: Pres Obama, once ambivalent about executive power, will leave office having employed executive power to pass 560 major regulations, making him one of most prolific regulatory authors in presidential history; Obama's slow embrace of unilateral action was driven by resistance in Congress and will likely shape presidency for decades to come (Series: The Obama Era).
